  "text": "The Kubernetes scheduler plugin framework is organized into multiple layers:\n\n**Framework Interface Definitions (pkg/scheduler/framework/interface.go):**\nThe core plugin interfaces are defined here:\n- Plugin: Base interface that all plugins must implement, requiring a Name() method\n- PreFilterPlugin: Runs at the beginning of the scheduling cycle to filter nodes or reject the pod\n- FilterPlugin: Runs after PreFilter to eliminate nodes that cannot run the pod\n- PostFilterPlugin: Runs when scheduling fails to enable preemption or other recovery mechanisms\n- ScorePlugin: Ranks filtered nodes based on scoring criteria\n- ReservePlugin: Updates internal state when a pod is assumed on a node, with Unreserve for cleanup\n- PreBindPlugin: Runs before binding to perform final checks\n- PostBindPlugin: Informational plugin that runs after successful binding\n- PermitPlugin: Can prevent or delay pod binding with timeout support\n- BindPlugin: Actually binds the pod to the selected node\n- Framework: Manages plugins and their invocation orchestration\n\n**Cycle State Management (pkg/scheduler/framework/cycle_state.go):**\nCycleState stores framework data during a scheduling cycle, allowing plugins to share state and data across extension points.\n\n**Runtime Framework Implementation (pkg/scheduler/framework/runtime/framework.go):**\nThe frameworkImpl struct implements the Framework interface and provides methods to invoke plugins:\n- RunPreFilterPlugins: Invokes all PreFilter plugins\n- RunFilterPlugins: Invokes Filter plugins in parallel across nodes\n- RunPostFilterPlugins: Invokes PostFilter plugins when filtering fails\n- RunScorePlugins: Scores filtered nodes using Score plugins\n- RunReservePluginsReserve: Reserves the pod on the selected node\n- RunReservePluginsUnreserve: Unreserves if subsequent plugins fail\n- RunPermitPlugins: Gets permit approval before binding\n- RunPreBindPlugins: Runs pre-binding checks\n- RunBindPlugins: Performs the actual bin